<section id="chapter1" class="chapter chapter--part-number" data-canonical='https://www.usatoday.com/in-depth/news/nation/2022/12/31/all-ages-drag-show-roanoke-texas-protest/10929001002/' data-share-parent='true' data-share-headline='A drag show, a protest and a line of guns: How the battle over one issue is tearing at America'>
	<div
	class="custom-chapter-marker no-image bg-color sans-serif"
	id="part-one"
	data-position="top"
	data-layout="body-width"
	
	
	
>
	
	<h2 class="chapter-marker-header"  style="background-color: #7d1225;color: #EFEFEF !important;text-align: center !important;">PART ONE</h2>
	
</div>


</section>
		
		
<section id="chapter2" class="chapter chapter--part-title" data-canonical='https://www.usatoday.com/in-depth/news/nation/2022/12/31/all-ages-drag-show-roanoke-texas-protest/10929001002/' data-share-parent='true' data-share-headline='A drag show, a protest and a line of guns: How the battle over one issue is tearing at America'>
	<div
	class="custom-chapter-marker no-image serif"
	id="the-idea"
	data-position="top"
	data-layout="body-width"
	
	
	
>
	
	<h2 class="chapter-marker-header"  style="color: #2a2a2a !important;text-align: center !important;">THE IDEA</h2>
	
</div>


<p><span class="marker">IT&#39;S A CRISP FALL DAY</span> in North Texas, the sky shining as bright as the high-gloss paint on the &lsquo;62 Corvair in the classic car show staged on Oak Street downtown. The Corvair glows duckling yellow. The sky is robin&rsquo;s egg blue.</p>

<p>The air, after a fall rain, is a perfect 68 degrees. It&rsquo;s the kind of day that makes it possible, for a minute, <span class="exclude-from-newsgate">to forget the scorch of the Texas summer, </span>to imagine everything in the world is just right, exactly as it is.</p>

<p>The trees on Oak Street rustle in the breeze as people roam from one end of the street to the other, from north of the water tower to the south, ending at the new City Hall &mdash; all 30,000 square feet of it, with its sweeping staircase, clock tower and intricate tilework in the restrooms. The cars are on show, but people are also here for the free food from five restaurants. They&rsquo;re serving samples so everyone can have a taste and then vote online to pick a winner.&nbsp;</p>

<p>They&rsquo;re here for the food because Roanoke is all about restaurants. That&rsquo;s what turned this little city into a place &ndash; cemented in 2009 when friendly voices in Austin passed a resolution at the statehouse deeming this little city the &ldquo;Unique Dining Capital of Texas.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>

<figure data-layout='center' id='asset-10882899002' class='indepth-image  center-container zoomable' style='--img-height: 2000;--img-width: 3000;'>
	<img src='https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/30103f29-7a58-4ea8-93ea-3cac69d344ee-_JC15978.jpg' srcset='https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/30103f29-7a58-4ea8-93ea-3cac69d344ee-_JC15978.jpg?width=100 100w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/30103f29-7a58-4ea8-93ea-3cac69d344ee-_JC15978.jpg?width=200 200w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/30103f29-7a58-4ea8-93ea-3cac69d344ee-_JC15978.jpg?width=300 300w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/30103f29-7a58-4ea8-93ea-3cac69d344ee-_JC15978.jpg?width=600 600w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/30103f29-7a58-4ea8-93ea-3cac69d344ee-_JC15978.jpg?width=800 800w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/30103f29-7a58-4ea8-93ea-3cac69d344ee-_JC15978.jpg?width=1100 1100w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/30103f29-7a58-4ea8-93ea-3cac69d344ee-_JC15978.jpg?width=1500 1500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/30103f29-7a58-4ea8-93ea-3cac69d344ee-_JC15978.jpg?width=2000 2000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/30103f29-7a58-4ea8-93ea-3cac69d344ee-_JC15978.jpg?width=2500 2500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/30103f29-7a58-4ea8-93ea-3cac69d344ee-_JC15978.jpg?width=3000 3000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/30103f29-7a58-4ea8-93ea-3cac69d344ee-_JC15978.jpg?width=3500 3500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/30103f29-7a58-4ea8-93ea-3cac69d344ee-_JC15978.jpg?width=4000 4000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/30103f29-7a58-4ea8-93ea-3cac69d344ee-_JC15978.jpg?width=4500 4500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/30103f29-7a58-4ea8-93ea-3cac69d344ee-_JC15978.jpg?width=5000 5000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/30103f29-7a58-4ea8-93ea-3cac69d344ee-_JC15978.jpg?width=5500 5500w' sizes='(min-width: 1024px) 80vw, 100vw' alt='The sun sets over Roanoke City Hall in downtown Roanoke, Texas, a Dallas-Ft. Worth suburb that bills itself as a dining destination.' height='2000' width='3000' loading='lazy' />
	<div class="image-zoom__modal-trigger"></div>
	
	<figcaption class="indepth-image__caption">
		The sun sets over Roanoke City Hall in downtown Roanoke, Texas, a Dallas-Ft. Worth suburb that bills itself as a dining destination.
		<span class="indepth-image__credit">Jasper Colt-USA TODAY</span>
	</figcaption>
	
</figure>

<p>So the highlight of the veteran&rsquo;s parade and classic car show today might really be the cookoff, where restaurants serve up little slices of wood-fired or forkfuls of chicken-fried or, at Anderson Distillery, little cups of hot mac and cheese.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p>Barely a block up from the new City Hall, Jay Anderson is working the door and the cookoff at the same time, and a line is forming as he scoops macaroni shots.&nbsp;</p>

<p>It&rsquo;s easy to forget that a little more than two months earlier, in the heat of the Texas summer, Jay Anderson and his son, Bailey, opened up their doors for brunch and walked right into the middle of a fight that everybody knew was simmering, but nobody thought would ever explode in this<span class="exclude-from-newsgate"> little</span> city of 9,878 people.&nbsp;</p>

<p>But that explosion was very real. And it all happened because, in late August, the Andersons included three words when they posted a new event on the distillery&rsquo;s social media.&nbsp;</p>

<p>The event was a drag show &ndash; the Barrel Babes Drag Brunch. A drag show alone might have been enough to whip up a reaction in Roanoke. But the event posting included three other crucial words that were enough to shove Roanoke into the middle of the controversy that has&nbsp;roiled Texas and further split an already divided America in 2022. Three words:&nbsp;</p>

<p>ALL AGES WELCOME!&nbsp;</p>

<p>To the Andersons, it had seemed simple. There would be brunch. There would be families. And there would be drag performers &ndash; starting with Bailey, who had been performing in drag since 2017, while also helping build the family business.&nbsp;</p>

<p>Simple.</p>

<p>But from the start, things were complicated: The objections from City Hall, the email campaign to shut down&nbsp;Anderson Distillery,&nbsp;the laser focus of the prolific live-stream protester who travels with an entourage she says is usually armed.</p>

