    <div class="video-details title show-length">An all-ages drag brunch in Texas: Protesters and armed supporters</div>
    
    
    <div class="video-details caption">Protesters against an all-ages drag brunch in Roanoke, Texas, pushed the town into the middle of a larger controversy over the issue.</div>
    
    
    
    <div class="video-details attribution">Jasper Colt, USA TODAY</div>
    
	</div>
</div>


<p>It&rsquo;s hard to imagine that Bailey had called police departments for miles around and discovered that nobody would help with security. Or that a protest planned for the drag brunch caught the eye of the multiagency police fusion center in the next county over &mdash; the one that&rsquo;s tasked with watching for criminal activity and terrorism.&nbsp;</p>

<p>And, if all that wasn&rsquo;t enough, that was before the black-clad leftists showed up to protect Anderson Distillery&nbsp;and its clients, bringing their assault rifles and face masks and body armor to a standoff with conservative protesters.</p>

<p>Before the screaming and the public praying, the shouting about pedophiles and abuse and grooming and puberty blockers and a lot of things that were never really about Andersons&#39;, or brunch, or even drag, at all.</p>

<p>Before the people from the right-wing websites and YouTube channels showed up, before the false stories on Twitter and the outraged interviews on Fox News.</p>

<p>Before the Andersons&rsquo; landlord had them sign a promise they would never do this again, before they had to pin up the map they call the Wall of Hate just to keep track of all the abusive phone calls.</p>

<p>The Andersons know all that now. But there&rsquo;s something else they don&rsquo;t know yet.</p>

<figure data-layout='center-well' id='asset-10882900002' class='indepth-image  center-well zoomable' style='--img-height: 2000;--img-width: 3000;'>
	<img src='https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1089b70f-8ddb-4c34-babb-06f26b058949-_JC16053.jpg' srcset='https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1089b70f-8ddb-4c34-babb-06f26b058949-_JC16053.jpg?width=100 100w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1089b70f-8ddb-4c34-babb-06f26b058949-_JC16053.jpg?width=200 200w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1089b70f-8ddb-4c34-babb-06f26b058949-_JC16053.jpg?width=300 300w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1089b70f-8ddb-4c34-babb-06f26b058949-_JC16053.jpg?width=600 600w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1089b70f-8ddb-4c34-babb-06f26b058949-_JC16053.jpg?width=800 800w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1089b70f-8ddb-4c34-babb-06f26b058949-_JC16053.jpg?width=1100 1100w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1089b70f-8ddb-4c34-babb-06f26b058949-_JC16053.jpg?width=1500 1500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1089b70f-8ddb-4c34-babb-06f26b058949-_JC16053.jpg?width=2000 2000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1089b70f-8ddb-4c34-babb-06f26b058949-_JC16053.jpg?width=2500 2500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1089b70f-8ddb-4c34-babb-06f26b058949-_JC16053.jpg?width=3000 3000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1089b70f-8ddb-4c34-babb-06f26b058949-_JC16053.jpg?width=3500 3500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1089b70f-8ddb-4c34-babb-06f26b058949-_JC16053.jpg?width=4000 4000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1089b70f-8ddb-4c34-babb-06f26b058949-_JC16053.jpg?width=4500 4500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1089b70f-8ddb-4c34-babb-06f26b058949-_JC16053.jpg?width=5000 5000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1089b70f-8ddb-4c34-babb-06f26b058949-_JC16053.jpg?width=5500 5500w' sizes='(min-width: 768px) 64vw, (min-width: 1024px) 48vw, 100vw' alt='Roanoke, Texas, a city of 9,878, became just one flashpoint in a nationwide face-off in 2022. On the surface, the fight was about a drag show.' height='2000' width='3000' loading='lazy' />
	<div class="image-zoom__modal-trigger"></div>
	
	<figcaption class="indepth-image__caption">
		Roanoke, Texas, a city of 9,878, became just one flashpoint in a nationwide face-off in 2022. On the surface, the fight was about a drag show.
		<span class="indepth-image__credit">Jasper Colt-USA TODAY</span>
	</figcaption>
	
</figure>

<p>On this November day at the cookoff, the Andersons don&rsquo;t know that in just two weeks, another person in another state will walk into another bar hosting another drag show. That this person will be carrying an assault rifle and open fire. And that this &nbsp;time, there will be no armed leftists in body armor to stop what happens. Just patrons inside to do the tackling after the shooting begins.</p>

<p>They don&rsquo;t know&nbsp;now &mdash; nobody knows it, yet, but everybody will soon &mdash; that five people will be slaughtered  at that drag show, at that bar, in Colorado. That a performer from the drag show will be shot and killed. That it will happen on a Saturday night in a bar that is setting up to host an all-ages drag brunch on Sunday morning.</p>

<p>What they know right now in Roanoke is that it&rsquo;s the cookoff today.&nbsp;</p>

<p>Jay Anderson is sweating and breathless, rushing to fill more free samples as people appear at the door to await a table.&nbsp;</p>

<p>&ldquo;I&rsquo;ll be right there to seat you,&rdquo; he says. Then he makes a sharp right to the mac and cheese station&nbsp;and starts scooping a little faster.</p>

</section>
		
		<div
	class="custom-chapter-marker no-image"
	id="drag-in-america"
	data-position="top"
	data-layout="body-width"
	
	data-section-background-color='#DFDFDF' data-section=''
	
>
	
	<h2 class="chapter-marker-header"  style="color: #7d1225 !important;">Drag in America</h2>
	
</div>

		
		<p>All-ages drag shows have become the front line in America’s culture wars.</p>
		
		<p>Drag performances – classically, a show in which men dress in women’s clothing and perform under a female persona – are about as old as performance itself. History is filled with examples of men performing as women, from <a href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/bitesize/articles/zbkmkmn" target="_blank">Shakespeare</a> plays  to <a href="https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2014/01/03/cozy-movie-classics-for-a-cold-winters-night/4312613/" target="_blank">Billy Wilder movies</a> from the golden era of Hollywood. </p>
		
		<p>Drag performance for adults was often something akin to burlesque. But in the era of reality TV, drag also went mainstream. Performer <a href="https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2018/04/05/has-pop-culture-finally-caught-up-rupaul-10-seasons-drag-race/463659002/" target="_blank">RuPaul’s</a> 1992 radio hit about supermodels had kids across America singing the earworm “You better work.” His hit show “RuPaul’s Drag Race” burst onto television in 2009.</p>
		
		<p>By this decade, experts were estimating that <a href="https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2022/06/21/lgbtq-gay-pride-events-rural-usa/7611127001/" target="_blank">Pride events were reaching record numbers</a> in the country’s smallest towns. “<a href="https://www.nbcnews.com/nbc-out/out-pop-culture/rupaul-addresses-anti-drag-protests-attacks-pray-country-rcna62133" target="_blank">RuPaul’s Drag Race</a>” was headed toward its 15th season on the air.</p>
		
		<p>“Drag brunches,” where performers mingle with a mimosa-vibed crowd, could be found in most of America’s big cities.</p>
		
		<p>Drag performers and experts say drag is about freedom of expression, about joy, about feeling glamorous and beautiful and outrageous.</p>
		
		<figure data-layout='center-well' id='asset-6583597002' class='indepth-image  center-well zoomable' style='--img-height: 1702;--img-width: 2568;'>
	<img loading='lazy' src='https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2021/01/07/USAT/3adee4bd-148f-4ea5-87ae-cc5941b41875-Screen_Shot_2021-01-07_at_1.36.59_PM.png' srcset='https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2021/01/07/USAT/3adee4bd-148f-4ea5-87ae-cc5941b41875-Screen_Shot_2021-01-07_at_1.36.59_PM.png?width=100 100w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2021/01/07/USAT/3adee4bd-148f-4ea5-87ae-cc5941b41875-Screen_Shot_2021-01-07_at_1.36.59_PM.png?width=200 200w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2021/01/07/USAT/3adee4bd-148f-4ea5-87ae-cc5941b41875-Screen_Shot_2021-01-07_at_1.36.59_PM.png?width=300 300w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2021/01/07/USAT/3adee4bd-148f-4ea5-87ae-cc5941b41875-Screen_Shot_2021-01-07_at_1.36.59_PM.png?width=600 600w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2021/01/07/USAT/3adee4bd-148f-4ea5-87ae-cc5941b41875-Screen_Shot_2021-01-07_at_1.36.59_PM.png?width=800 800w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2021/01/07/USAT/3adee4bd-148f-4ea5-87ae-cc5941b41875-Screen_Shot_2021-01-07_at_1.36.59_PM.png?width=1100 1100w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2021/01/07/USAT/3adee4bd-148f-4ea5-87ae-cc5941b41875-Screen_Shot_2021-01-07_at_1.36.59_PM.png?width=1500 1500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2021/01/07/USAT/3adee4bd-148f-4ea5-87ae-cc5941b41875-Screen_Shot_2021-01-07_at_1.36.59_PM.png?width=2000 2000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2021/01/07/USAT/3adee4bd-148f-4ea5-87ae-cc5941b41875-Screen_Shot_2021-01-07_at_1.36.59_PM.png?width=2500 2500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2021/01/07/USAT/3adee4bd-148f-4ea5-87ae-cc5941b41875-Screen_Shot_2021-01-07_at_1.36.59_PM.png?width=3000 3000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2021/01/07/USAT/3adee4bd-148f-4ea5-87ae-cc5941b41875-Screen_Shot_2021-01-07_at_1.36.59_PM.png?width=3500 3500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2021/01/07/USAT/3adee4bd-148f-4ea5-87ae-cc5941b41875-Screen_Shot_2021-01-07_at_1.36.59_PM.png?width=4000 4000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2021/01/07/USAT/3adee4bd-148f-4ea5-87ae-cc5941b41875-Screen_Shot_2021-01-07_at_1.36.59_PM.png?width=4500 4500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2021/01/07/USAT/3adee4bd-148f-4ea5-87ae-cc5941b41875-Screen_Shot_2021-01-07_at_1.36.59_PM.png?width=5000 5000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2021/01/07/USAT/3adee4bd-148f-4ea5-87ae-cc5941b41875-Screen_Shot_2021-01-07_at_1.36.59_PM.png?width=5500 5500w' sizes='(min-width: 768px) 64vw, (min-width: 1024px) 48vw, 100vw' alt='&#34;RuPaul&#39;s Drag Race&#34; host RuPaul with judges Michelle Visage, Carson Kressley and Ross Mathews. Fueled in part by RuPaul&#39;s perennial cultural presence, drag shows went mainstream. But along the way, they also polarized America.' height='1702' width='2568' />
	<div class="image-zoom__modal-trigger"></div>
	
	<figcaption class="indepth-image__caption">
		&#34;RuPaul&#39;s Drag Race&#34; host RuPaul with judges Michelle Visage, Carson Kressley and Ross Mathews. Fueled in part by RuPaul&#39;s perennial cultural presence, drag shows went mainstream. But along the way, they also polarized America.
		<span class="indepth-image__credit">Contributed by VH1</span>
	</figcaption>
	
</figure>
		
		<p>But they will also tell you it can be about something more than entertainment.</p>
		
		<p>For some people, drag is a proxy for LGBTQ pride and a form of acceptance. To some, a drag show, particularly, is a vibrant demonstration for people who feel different, one that tells them: It’s OK for you to be different, too.</p>
		
		<p>But somewhere in the midst of all that pop-culture acceptance, something got polarized in America. And while it wasn’t exactly all about drag performance, it was, people said, all about children.</p>
		
		<p>To some people, it seemed more children than ever were questioning their gender, their own identity. And as the nation grappled with difficult questions about transgender rights, medical care for children questioning their gender and their parents’ right to help them, all-ages drag shows became a proxy battleground for these complex debates.</p>
		
		<p>Because drag shows have traditionally featured risque content, crude language and even nudity or partial nudity, many Americans questioned why all-ages drag shows even exist. Fed by conservative media, conspiracy theories erupted about these events: They aimed to expose children to sexual activity, opponents said. Or to make them transgender. Or lure them into the hands of sexually abusive drag queens.</p>
		
		<p>As summer 2022 boiled on, drag performances — especially all-ages drag shows — triggered organized protest movements, raucous demonstrations and sporadic violence across the country. Faceoffs and protests happened in Denton, Texas, and Katy, Texas. Woodland, California, and Eugene, Oregon. Iowa City, Iowa, and Memphis, Tennessee.  </p>
		
		<figure data-layout='center' id='asset-9606693002' class='indepth-image  center-container zoomable' style='--img-height: 1705;--img-width: 2400;'>
	<img srcset='https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/05/01/PLSJ/58a4c3a9-e565-42cc-91cc-cb9af0d79ca8-Drag_Brunch-1.jpg?width=100 100w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/05/01/PLSJ/58a4c3a9-e565-42cc-91cc-cb9af0d79ca8-Drag_Brunch-1.jpg?width=200 200w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/05/01/PLSJ/58a4c3a9-e565-42cc-91cc-cb9af0d79ca8-Drag_Brunch-1.jpg?width=300 300w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/05/01/PLSJ/58a4c3a9-e565-42cc-91cc-cb9af0d79ca8-Drag_Brunch-1.jpg?width=600 600w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/05/01/PLSJ/58a4c3a9-e565-42cc-91cc-cb9af0d79ca8-Drag_Brunch-1.jpg?width=800 800w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/05/01/PLSJ/58a4c3a9-e565-42cc-91cc-cb9af0d79ca8-Drag_Brunch-1.jpg?width=1100 1100w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/05/01/PLSJ/58a4c3a9-e565-42cc-91cc-cb9af0d79ca8-Drag_Brunch-1.jpg?width=1500 1500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/05/01/PLSJ/58a4c3a9-e565-42cc-91cc-cb9af0d79ca8-Drag_Brunch-1.jpg?width=2000 2000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/05/01/PLSJ/58a4c3a9-e565-42cc-91cc-cb9af0d79ca8-Drag_Brunch-1.jpg?width=2500 2500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/05/01/PLSJ/58a4c3a9-e565-42cc-91cc-cb9af0d79ca8-Drag_Brunch-1.jpg?width=3000 3000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/05/01/PLSJ/58a4c3a9-e565-42cc-91cc-cb9af0d79ca8-Drag_Brunch-1.jpg?width=3500 3500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/05/01/PLSJ/58a4c3a9-e565-42cc-91cc-cb9af0d79ca8-Drag_Brunch-1.jpg?width=4000 4000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/05/01/PLSJ/58a4c3a9-e565-42cc-91cc-cb9af0d79ca8-Drag_Brunch-1.jpg?width=4500 4500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/05/01/PLSJ/58a4c3a9-e565-42cc-91cc-cb9af0d79ca8-Drag_Brunch-1.jpg?width=5000 5000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/05/01/PLSJ/58a4c3a9-e565-42cc-91cc-cb9af0d79ca8-Drag_Brunch-1.jpg?width=5500 5500w' sizes='(min-width: 1024px) 80vw, 100vw' alt='Aaliyah Tealheart performs in drag for a fundraiser in Lansing, Michigan, in April 2022. By 2022, drag had long been mainstream in American. But shows were also spurring a protest movement.' height='1705' width='2400' loading='lazy' src='https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/05/01/PLSJ/58a4c3a9-e565-42cc-91cc-cb9af0d79ca8-Drag_Brunch-1.jpg' />
	<div class="image-zoom__modal-trigger"></div>
	
	<figcaption class="indepth-image__caption">
		Aaliyah Tealheart performs in drag for a fundraiser in Lansing, Michigan, in April 2022. By 2022, drag had long been mainstream in American. But shows were also spurring a protest movement.
		<span class="indepth-image__credit">Robert Killips | Lansing State Journal</span>
	</figcaption>
	
</figure>
		
		<p>Soon, videos captured at some of these events became features on Fox News prime time and conspiracy theory websites. Snippets of video showed performers using dirty words or zoomed in on faces of children who appeared uncomfortable. Outraged commentators filled in the gaps.</p>
		
		<p>Like other targets that preceded them in polarized America — critical race theory, COVID-19 vaccine mandates, the idea of white privilege — all-ages drag events became a new moral battleground.</p>
		
		<p>Some conservatives, joined by extremists from the far right including white supremacists and members of the street gang the Proud Boys, say they are stepping in to quite literally stop abusers and pedophiles from preying on innocent children.</p>
		
		<p>On the other side, drag performers, the businesses who host them and pro-LGBTQ groups say all-ages drag shows help break down stigmas and serve as a vital lifeline to children experiencing confusion about their gender identity. The goal with these shows is to express camaraderie: to make an overt display of solidarity by appearing<span class="exclude-from-newsgate">, in person,</span> in the neighborhoods where those children live, those groups say.</p>
		
		<p>Children experiencing gender dysphoria — distress based on the difference between the gender they experience and the gender they were assigned at birth — are far more likely to harm themselves or die of suicide, said Sam Ames, director of advocacy and government affairs at the Trevor Project, a mental health organization for LGBTQ young people.</p>
		
		<div class="center-container" id="10959948002"   data-in-view-event='shareable-quote' >
