</div>
		
		<p>She’s never sat down and talked with the Trevor Project, to hear how these shows impact transgender and questioning children’s mental health. She’s never spoken to a drag performer who performs for children. Or a proponent of the shows. Or an academic who has studied them. </p>
		
		<p>She told USA TODAY she’s open to doing so, though she doesn’t really see the point.</p>
		
		<p>“I would be totally willing to sit down with someone,” she said. “I don&#39;t think at the end of the day, my mind would be changed.”</p>
		
		<p>Neidert also talked to USA TODAY about another hot-button topic that helped Roanoke make the news: Second Amendment rights. </p>
		
		<p>Sometimes she said, she and her supporters will openly carry guns at events, which is legal in Texas. More often, they’re carrying for protection, she said. </p>
		
		<p>“Typically when I go out, if people on my side aren&#39;t carrying, I think that they&#39;re typically concealed carrying,” Neidert said. </p>
		
		<p>Whatever her motivations, Neidert and her group get attention. When the Andersons were organizing their event, she had already been on cable news shows and was making a mark in the right-wing media realm. </p>
		
		<p>So when Protect Texas Kids posted its pop-up protest, people who followed right-wing media noticed, fast.</p>
		
		<p>Her post became a kind of force multiplier for Anderson Distillery. </p>
		
		<p>But it got the restaurant noticed by all the kinds of people who weren’t interested in going to a drag brunch.</p>
		
		<div
	class="custom-chapter-marker no-image"
	id="storm-at-city"
	data-position="top"
	data-layout="body-width"
	
	data-section-background-color='#CFCFCF' data-section=''
	
>
	
	<h2 class="chapter-marker-header"  style="color: #7d1225 !important;">Storm at City Hall </h2>
	
</div>

		
		<p>On the same day Protect Texas Kids announced its protest, city officials were talking a lot — to one another.  </p>
		
		<p>At 5:23 p.m., Roanoke Councilmember Bryan Moyers wrote an email to the mayor and city manager Campbell: </p>
		
		<p>“Have y’all seen this?” he asked. “I don’t like it at all. Doesn’t align with our core values.” </p>
		
		<figure id='asset-10964715002' class='indepth-image  center-well zoomable' style='--img-height: 574;--img-width: 1749;' data-layout='center-well'>
	<img loading='lazy' src='https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/07877918-ca92-47ba-92fa-76a15533fed5-tearsheets_2.jpg' srcset='https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/07877918-ca92-47ba-92fa-76a15533fed5-tearsheets_2.jpg?width=100 100w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/07877918-ca92-47ba-92fa-76a15533fed5-tearsheets_2.jpg?width=200 200w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/07877918-ca92-47ba-92fa-76a15533fed5-tearsheets_2.jpg?width=300 300w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/07877918-ca92-47ba-92fa-76a15533fed5-tearsheets_2.jpg?width=600 600w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/07877918-ca92-47ba-92fa-76a15533fed5-tearsheets_2.jpg?width=800 800w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/07877918-ca92-47ba-92fa-76a15533fed5-tearsheets_2.jpg?width=1100 1100w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/07877918-ca92-47ba-92fa-76a15533fed5-tearsheets_2.jpg?width=1500 1500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/07877918-ca92-47ba-92fa-76a15533fed5-tearsheets_2.jpg?width=2000 2000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/07877918-ca92-47ba-92fa-76a15533fed5-tearsheets_2.jpg?width=2500 2500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/07877918-ca92-47ba-92fa-76a15533fed5-tearsheets_2.jpg?width=3000 3000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/07877918-ca92-47ba-92fa-76a15533fed5-tearsheets_2.jpg?width=3500 3500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/07877918-ca92-47ba-92fa-76a15533fed5-tearsheets_2.jpg?width=4000 4000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/07877918-ca92-47ba-92fa-76a15533fed5-tearsheets_2.jpg?width=4500 4500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/07877918-ca92-47ba-92fa-76a15533fed5-tearsheets_2.jpg?width=5000 5000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/07877918-ca92-47ba-92fa-76a15533fed5-tearsheets_2.jpg?width=5500 5500w' sizes='(min-width: 768px) 64vw, (min-width: 1024px) 48vw, 100vw' alt='A Roanoke city email obtained by USA TODAY.' height='574' width='1749' />
	<div class="image-zoom__modal-trigger"></div>
	
</figure>
		
		<p>Six minutes after that, at 5:29 p.m., Campbell replied to Moyers, writing that the city had received complaints about the brunch, but that the event did not appear to need a special permit, and the city probably couldn’t stop it. </p>
		
		<p>At 6:18 p.m., Campbell wrote to the entire city council, saying he had heard there would be protests at the Anderson Distillery event.  </p>
		
		<p>By the next day, angry emails were landing in the city council’s inboxes. </p>
		
		<p>“When did sexually oriented businesses become a thing in this town?” wrote one resident, who said he had lived in Roanoke for more than 20 years. “This is highly inappropriate and to welcome all ages is completely inexcusable and should not be tolerated.”</p>
		
		<p>Mayor Gierisch’s responses were rapid-fire.</p>
		
		<p>“We are looking at every legal statute to see if there is a provision that we could take action,” he wrote. “I’ve personally reached out to the owner and his landlord. I’ve encouraged people to reach out to Jay Anderson and share the dissatisfaction.” </p>
		
		<figure data-layout='center-well' id='asset-10964716002' class='indepth-image  center-well zoomable' style='--img-height: 1020;--img-width: 1216;'>
	<img alt='A Roanoke city email obtained by USA TODAY.' height='1020' width='1216' loading='lazy' src='https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/b58b92e5-bfb0-4278-9420-6db349381f84-tearsheets_4.jpg' srcset='https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/b58b92e5-bfb0-4278-9420-6db349381f84-tearsheets_4.jpg?width=100 100w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/b58b92e5-bfb0-4278-9420-6db349381f84-tearsheets_4.jpg?width=200 200w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/b58b92e5-bfb0-4278-9420-6db349381f84-tearsheets_4.jpg?width=300 300w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/b58b92e5-bfb0-4278-9420-6db349381f84-tearsheets_4.jpg?width=600 600w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/b58b92e5-bfb0-4278-9420-6db349381f84-tearsheets_4.jpg?width=800 800w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/b58b92e5-bfb0-4278-9420-6db349381f84-tearsheets_4.jpg?width=1100 1100w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/b58b92e5-bfb0-4278-9420-6db349381f84-tearsheets_4.jpg?width=1500 1500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/b58b92e5-bfb0-4278-9420-6db349381f84-tearsheets_4.jpg?width=2000 2000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/b58b92e5-bfb0-4278-9420-6db349381f84-tearsheets_4.jpg?width=2500 2500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/b58b92e5-bfb0-4278-9420-6db349381f84-tearsheets_4.jpg?width=3000 3000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/b58b92e5-bfb0-4278-9420-6db349381f84-tearsheets_4.jpg?width=3500 3500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/b58b92e5-bfb0-4278-9420-6db349381f84-tearsheets_4.jpg?width=4000 4000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/b58b92e5-bfb0-4278-9420-6db349381f84-tearsheets_4.jpg?width=4500 4500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/b58b92e5-bfb0-4278-9420-6db349381f84-tearsheets_4.jpg?width=5000 5000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/29/USAT/b58b92e5-bfb0-4278-9420-6db349381f84-tearsheets_4.jpg?width=5500 5500w' sizes='(min-width: 768px) 64vw, (min-width: 1024px) 48vw, 100vw' />
	<div class="image-zoom__modal-trigger"></div>
	
</figure>
		
		<p>Jay Anderson said Gierisch never tried to convince him to cancel the event. Gierisch, Moyers and every other Roanoke city council member, when contacted by USA TODAY, declined to comment about the event at Anderson’s or did not respond.</p>
		
		<p>On that same day, Aug. 18, the Texas Scorecard, a conservative website, published a story about the planned Barrel Babes Brunch. </p>
		
		<p>“Roanoke Restaurant Poised to Hold Drag Show for Children,” the headline read.</p>
		
		<p>With the right-wing media coverage growing, the turmoil was also spreading well beyond City Hall.</p>
		
		<p>On Roanoke’s Fairway Ranch neighborhood Facebook page, the usual gripes focused on why the underpass on Byron Nelson Boulevard was once again closed, or the pack of wild hogs wandering in front of Cox Elementary.</p>
		
		<p>Now, a member posted a link to the Texas Scorecard story, urging people to write to the restaurant and “step up in any way you can to show that this isn’t the draw we want for our downtown!”</p>
		
		<p>Here, too, Gierisch jumped in. He quickly posted in the Facebook group that the city was on top of the problem. He even gave people Jay Anderson’s direct email address.</p>
		
		<p>More angry emails came in: “This is nothing short of child abuse.” “This is disgusting and should be illegal.” “This is just as bad as porn.”  </p>
		
		<figure data-layout='center-well' id='asset-10970052002' class='indepth-image  center-well zoomable' style='--img-height: 927;--img-width: 1854;'>
	<img src='https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/30/USAT/06a55591-2077-409d-a5b0-0ea3b39ee45b-tearsheets_5v2.jpg' srcset='https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/30/USAT/06a55591-2077-409d-a5b0-0ea3b39ee45b-tearsheets_5v2.jpg?width=100 100w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/30/USAT/06a55591-2077-409d-a5b0-0ea3b39ee45b-tearsheets_5v2.jpg?width=200 200w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/30/USAT/06a55591-2077-409d-a5b0-0ea3b39ee45b-tearsheets_5v2.jpg?width=300 300w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/30/USAT/06a55591-2077-409d-a5b0-0ea3b39ee45b-tearsheets_5v2.jpg?width=600 600w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/30/USAT/06a55591-2077-409d-a5b0-0ea3b39ee45b-tearsheets_5v2.jpg?width=800 800w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/30/USAT/06a55591-2077-409d-a5b0-0ea3b39ee45b-tearsheets_5v2.jpg?width=1100 1100w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/30/USAT/06a55591-2077-409d-a5b0-0ea3b39ee45b-tearsheets_5v2.jpg?width=1500 1500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/30/USAT/06a55591-2077-409d-a5b0-0ea3b39ee45b-tearsheets_5v2.jpg?width=2000 2000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/30/USAT/06a55591-2077-409d-a5b0-0ea3b39ee45b-tearsheets_5v2.jpg?width=2500 2500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/30/USAT/06a55591-2077-409d-a5b0-0ea3b39ee45b-tearsheets_5v2.jpg?width=3000 3000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/30/USAT/06a55591-2077-409d-a5b0-0ea3b39ee45b-tearsheets_5v2.jpg?width=3500 3500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/30/USAT/06a55591-2077-409d-a5b0-0ea3b39ee45b-tearsheets_5v2.jpg?width=4000 4000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/30/USAT/06a55591-2077-409d-a5b0-0ea3b39ee45b-tearsheets_5v2.jpg?width=4500 4500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/30/USAT/06a55591-2077-409d-a5b0-0ea3b39ee45b-tearsheets_5v2.jpg?width=5000 5000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/30/USAT/06a55591-2077-409d-a5b0-0ea3b39ee45b-tearsheets_5v2.jpg?width=5500 5500w' sizes='(min-width: 768px) 64vw, (min-width: 1024px) 48vw, 100vw' alt='Caption needed' height='927' width='1854' loading='lazy' />
	<div class="image-zoom__modal-trigger"></div>
	
</figure>
		
		<p>By Aug. 25, the city was fielding inquiries from reporters. And a lot of angry questions that boiled down to one thing: Why don’t you stop this?</p>
		
		<p>The City Council seemed convinced the Andersons planned to violate the very essence of Roanoke. But the city couldn’t find so much as a zoning violation. </p>
		
		<p>“It has been suggested that we should be treating Anderson’s as a Sexually Oriented Business because of the nature of the event.” wrote the city manager in an email to the council. “The City Attorney agrees that we cannot arbitrarily make that assumption unless we become aware of specific activity that falls into defined categories of our SOB ordinance.” </p>
		
		<p>Instead, the council knew that public pressure was their best weapon against the event. And Jay Anderson was getting lots of it.</p>
		
		<p>Now, he and his family had a decision to make.</p>
		
		<div
	class="custom-chapter-marker no-image"
	id="the-drag-performer"
	data-position="top"
	data-layout="body-width"
	
	data-section-background-color='#DFDFDF' data-section=''
	
>
	
	<h2 class="chapter-marker-header"  style="color: #7d1225 !important;">The drag performer</h2>
	
</div>

		
		<p>RuPaul once said: “When you become the image of your own imagination, it&#39;s the most powerful thing you could ever do.”</p>
		
		<p>That quote might define every side of the fight that happened in Roanoke. It’s meant to define the drag performer. But instead, it could be defining drag protesters. </p>
		
		<p>What actually happens at all-ages drag shows may be eclipsed by an imaginary version of what happened. Or might happen.</p>
		
		<figure style='--img-height: 2000;--img-width: 3000;' data-layout='center' id='asset-10882906002' class='indepth-image  center-container zoomable'>
	<img src='https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1c953d83-0705-47c5-b5c0-81f11c2391d1-_JC16104.jpg' srcset='https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1c953d83-0705-47c5-b5c0-81f11c2391d1-_JC16104.jpg?width=100 100w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1c953d83-0705-47c5-b5c0-81f11c2391d1-_JC16104.jpg?width=200 200w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1c953d83-0705-47c5-b5c0-81f11c2391d1-_JC16104.jpg?width=300 300w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1c953d83-0705-47c5-b5c0-81f11c2391d1-_JC16104.jpg?width=600 600w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1c953d83-0705-47c5-b5c0-81f11c2391d1-_JC16104.jpg?width=800 800w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1c953d83-0705-47c5-b5c0-81f11c2391d1-_JC16104.jpg?width=1100 1100w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1c953d83-0705-47c5-b5c0-81f11c2391d1-_JC16104.jpg?width=1500 1500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1c953d83-0705-47c5-b5c0-81f11c2391d1-_JC16104.jpg?width=2000 2000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1c953d83-0705-47c5-b5c0-81f11c2391d1-_JC16104.jpg?width=2500 2500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1c953d83-0705-47c5-b5c0-81f11c2391d1-_JC16104.jpg?width=3000 3000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1c953d83-0705-47c5-b5c0-81f11c2391d1-_JC16104.jpg?width=3500 3500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1c953d83-0705-47c5-b5c0-81f11c2391d1-_JC16104.jpg?width=4000 4000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1c953d83-0705-47c5-b5c0-81f11c2391d1-_JC16104.jpg?width=4500 4500w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1c953d83-0705-47c5-b5c0-81f11c2391d1-_JC16104.jpg?width=5000 5000w,https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2022/12/12/USAT/1c953d83-0705-47c5-b5c0-81f11c2391d1-_JC16104.jpg?width=5500 5500w' sizes='(min-width: 1024px) 80vw, 100vw' alt='Kiba Walker, a professional drag queen who performs as Salem Moon, applies makeup at the vanity in his bedroom in Fort Worth, Texas.' height='2000' width='3000' loading='lazy' />
	<div class="image-zoom__modal-trigger"></div>
	
	<figcaption class="indepth-image__caption">
		Kiba Walker, a professional drag queen who performs as Salem Moon, applies makeup at the vanity in his bedroom in Fort Worth, Texas.
		<span class="indepth-image__credit">Jasper Colt-USA TODAY</span>
	</figcaption>
	
</figure>
		
		<p>Kiba Walker, a Texas drag artist who performs as Salem Moon, said he’s perplexed at the ignorance and hate performers increasingly face. </p>
		
		<p>“To think that there are people out there saying that kids being exposed to this is dangerous to them, it kind of blows my mind,” Walker said. </p>
		
		<p>“I literally know kids that have tried to take their own lives because of the type of oppression and bullying that they got.”</p>
		
		<p>Walker began questioning his sexuality at the age of nine, and said he grew up facing brute hostility to the personal qualities he felt most enriched him and made him happiest.</p>
		
		<p>“I was obsessed with singing. I was obsessed with acting. I wanted to dress up and do all this other stuff, and kids and even adults would tell me ‘You can&#39;t do that,’” he said. </p>
		
		<p>Growing up in California in the 2000s, Walker said, classmates called him “gay” like it was a bad thing. He didn’t even know what the word meant.</p>
		
		<p>It got so bad, his parents decided to home-school him. But by the time Walker reached high school in Reno, Nevada, he found a group of friends who loved him for his art and his singing and acting and passion. Drag became a natural extension of that. It gave him a place to express himself, create his own narrative and live it out on stage.</p>
		
		<div class="center-container" id="10960830002"   data-in-view-event='shareable-quote' >
