    <figcaption class="component--pullquote__attribution">Stanislav Vysotsky, a professor of criminology</figcaption>
    <blockquote class="component--pullquote__text"><span>They are taking on another more proactive stance, particularly because the far-right have become increasingly more militarized. So they (anti-fascists) are becoming increasingly more armed — they’re becoming increasingly more intimidating as a way of demonstrating that people on the left won't be intimidated and will protect themselves.</span></blockquote>
    
